frameDefinitions: A Host provides a temporary Residence for a Lodger.
An Agent, Actor, Entity, or Medium causes a Phenomenon to be perceived by a Perceiver.
One Part of a larger Whole has been mentioned, is inferrable, or is available in the discourse setting and the previously unmentioned part, the Rest, is now mentioned.
A Distributor sells, lends, or otherwise distributes a class of Goods.

Some Possessor, either a nation, institution, or private individual, controls a Force whose primary functions to defend the Possessor (or, in the case of an institution or individual, some area of land significant to them) and to carry out offensive actions for the Possessor.
A Location is filled or covered with the Theme.
frameExamples: We <t>housed</t> her in our home for a while.
The lenses , like the <t><fex name='Rest'>rest</fex></t> of the exoskeleton, are made of calcite.
Trader Joe's <t>carries</t> a wide variety of foods, drinks, and househole necessities.
The waters of the bay <t>teemed</t> with fish.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Host</fen> is the individual (or group of individuals) that own or control the <fen>Residence</fen> and allow the  <fen>Lodger</fen> to temporarily stay there.
The <fen>Lodger</fen> is the individual who is given permission to lodge in the <fen>Residence</fen>.
The location controlled by the <fen>Host</fen> which the <fen>Lodger</fen> stays at temporarily.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Host</fen> provides a Residence to the <fen>Lodger</fen>
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the <fen>Host</fen> provides a temporary <fen>Residence</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> intentionally creates a situation in which the <fen>Perceiver</fen> observes or experiences the <fen>Phenomenon</fen>.
The <fen>Phenomenon</fen> is an entity or idea that is perceived by the <fen>Perceiver</fen>.
The <fen>Perceiver</fen> is made to have a perceptual experience by the <fen>Agent</fen>.
An <fen>Actor</fen> is a sentient being who is exhibiting, possibly uninintentionally, some <fen>Phenomenon</fen>.
An object that has some association with a <fen>Phenomenon</fen>.
The <fen>Medium</fen> through which a <fen>Phenomenon</fen> is expressed.
When the event occurs.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> causes the perception of the <fen>Perceiver</fen>.
A <fen>Part</fen> of a larger <fen>Whole</fen> that has been mentioned in prior discourse or is available in the discourse setting.
The previously unmentioned part of the <fen>Whole</fen>.
The larger entitiy or group that is fully made up of the <fen>Part</fen> and the <fen>Rest</fen>.
The <fen>Distributor</fen> maintains a store of <fen>Goods</fen> for the purpose of selling or otherwise distributing them.
The <fen>Goods</fen> are kept on hand and distributed by the <fen>Distributor</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Distributor</fen> carries the <fen>Goods</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates where the carrying of <fen>Goods</fen> occurs.
The <fen>Force</fen> is the body of soldiers that acts in military capacity for the <fen>Possessor</fen>. This role is incorporated in each word in this frame.
The <fen>Possessor</fen> is the nation, institution, or individual who possesses and/or controls the <fen>Force</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> covers or fills the <fen>Location</fen>.  This role most frequently occurs in a PP Complement headed by with or in.
<fen>Location</fen> is the object or area that the <fen>Theme</fen> fills or covers.  This frame element generally occurs as the External Argument.
The period of time during which the the Abounding_with event occurs.
listRoleExamples: the GP had stipulated counselling as a complement <fex>to medication</fex>
You should try to persuade the <fex>rest</fex> of the family to do so whatever their personal opinions
The American invasion, which drew 26000 American troops against <fex>General Noriega's</fex> army, was the largest US military operation since Vietnam.
The waters of the bay teemed <fex>with fish</fex>.
<fex>The walls</fex> crawled with nanite surveillance probes.
